cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.IT 

This paper discusses the security of instrumented environments, specifically building automation systems, which involves networking and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also focuses on security requirements, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper proposes a concrete security architecture, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses implementation and experimental results, which could place it in cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
